# Social Intelligence Agent (SIA) v2.0

Background agent that separates insider accumulation from retail noise across
X and Farcaster. Runs on a 1-hour cadence inside the Trader Sentinel cycle.
Writes all output to Supabase `token_signals` table (sia_* columns).

---

## Core Concepts

### Why Two Platforms

X (Twitter) has high volume but low signal-to-noise: retail, bots, KOL pumps,
and sponsored content dominate. Farcaster is smaller, more technical, and
populated by founders, developers, and early protocol participants. The
divergence between the two platforms is the alpha:

| Farcaster | X    | Signal | Interpretation |
|-----------|------|--------|----------------|
| High      | Low  | ACCUMULATION | Insiders active before retail notices |
| High      | High | PEAK | Narrative at maximum — watch for reversal |
| Low       | High | FOMO_RISK | Retail FOMO / KOL dump risk |
| Low       | Low  | ZOMBIE | No activity — token dead or dormant |

### Authority Tiers

| Tier | Authority Score | Examples |
|------|----------------|----------|
| 0 — Founders / Core Devs | 10.0 | Protocol founders, core contributors, official accounts |
| 1 — OGs / Early Backers | 5.0 | Known early investors, respected protocol builders, technical OGs |
| 2 — Verified Community | 2.0 | Accounts followed by Tier 0/1, active for >1 year, >1K followers |
| 3 — Retail | 1.0 | All others passing the minimum filter |
| FILTERED | 0 | < 100 followers OR bot-score > 0.7 OR account age < 30 days |

**Authority multiplier x10**: accounts followed by Virtuals, Bankr, Bittensor,
or Fetch.ai official accounts get their base score multiplied by 10 for that
token's signals. Following is a proxy for protocol-level endorsement.

