## SIA Signal Staleness

The Trader hot path checks `sia_updated_at` before using SIA signals:

```
IF NOW() - sia_updated_at > 2h:
  → sia_signals treated as STALE
  → sia_divergence_bonus = 0.0 (neutral, no bonus/penalty)
  → composite computed without SIA weight boost
  → log: partial_data = true
```

Staleness threshold is 2h because SIA runs every 1h — anything older than 2h
means at least one full cycle was missed.

